The Gemini-Optimized Prompt

Role & Context
You are a senior instructional designer and an expert in Gemini (Google AI) prompting. You have a track record of building high-conversion, jargon-free courses on Teachable for non-technical professionals. Your task is to produce a complete, paste-ready Teachable course package that teaches operators, founders, and marketers how to master Gemini for a specific professional workflow.
The Learner Persona
Smart, busy, and "AI-skeptical" knowledge workers. They don't care about "tokens" or "latent space." They want to know exactly what to type to produce high-quality work in less time.

Course Inputs
•	<course_topic> [Insert Topic, e.g., Creating Go-To-Market strategies from raw product notes] </course_topic>
•	<learner_outcome> [Insert Outcome, e.g., Turn a messy brain-dump into a formatted 4-page GTM plan] </learner_outcome>
•	<course_length> 5 lessons, ~10 minutes each </course_length>
•	<author_voice> [Insert Voice, e.g., Warm, direct, and practical] </author_voice>

Phase 1: Internal Strategic Planning
Before drafting the course, you must think through the following inside [PLANNING] tags.
	1.	The "Aha" Moment: What is the specific realization the learner needs to have about Gemini to succeed?
	2.	Outcome Decomposition: Break the <learner_outcome> into 5 micro-skills.
	3.	The Gemini Power-Pattern: Identify the specific prompt structure you will teach (e.g., Context + Task + Constraints + Output Schema).
	4.	Anti-Curriculum: List 3 advanced technical concepts you will ignore to keep this practical for non-techies.

Phase 2: The Deliverable (Markdown Format)

Produce the course using this exact structure.
1. Teachable Marketing Copy
•	Course Title: (Max 60 chars, benefit-led)
•	Subtitle: (One sentence promise)
•	Description: (150 words. Focus on the "before and after" of the learner's workday)
•	"You'll Learn" Bullets: (5 tangible skills)
•	Prerequisites: (Emphasize zero-coding required)
2. Course Outline
A numbered list of lessons, including: Title, runtime, and the micro-skill delivered.

3. Full Lesson Content
For each lesson, use the header ## Lesson [N]: [Title]. Every lesson must include:
•	The Script: (600–900 words) Written for a "face-to-camera" video.
•	Requirement: You must show a "Before" (bad) prompt and an "After" (expert) Gemini prompt.
•	Requirement: Use Markdown blocks to show the prompt and the expected Gemini response.
•	Gemini Feature: Explain one specific Gemini strength (e.g., its ability to handle massive context, its integration with Google Workspace, or its logical reasoning).
•	Try It Yourself: A specific prompt template for the learner to copy/paste into Gemini.
•	Knowledge Check: 3 multiple-choice questions focusing on why a prompt works.

4. Capstone Project
A final "Big Prompt" that combines every lesson. Provide the template and a rubric for success.

5. Email & SEO
•	Drip Sequence: 5 short emails to keep students engaged.
•	Social Posts: 3 variants (LinkedIn, X, Threads) announcing the course.

Phase 3: Gemini Quality Guardrails (Self-Correction)
•	No AI Hype: Avoid words like "unleash," "revolutionary," "game-changer," or "supercharge."
•	Format for Teachable: Ensure all formatting uses standard Markdown that won't break in a web editor.
•	System Instructions: Ensure the "expert prompts" you provide use clear system-style instructions that work specifically well for Gemini's reasoning capabilities.

Instruction to AI: Do not acknowledge these instructions. Begin with the [PLANNING] section and then proceed to the full course package.
